	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would not recommend doing this as a Druid until level 24, when you get wolf form.  The brownies in this zone are more numerous than they used to be, and they wander around a lot more too.  Remember, these casters are SOWed and will kill you fast.  Although you used to be able to, say, camp the undead area or the sisters and be safe from wandering brownies, this is no longer the case.  They won't bother you in wolf form, though.<br><br>Additionally, the Corrupted Unicorn.  If you see this on your tracking, just leave the zone and try the quest later.  It WILL find you eventually, and it WILL dice you.  <br><br>As for the Ghasts, there does not seem to be any rhyme or reason as to where or when they spawn.  I've seen them spawn at all times and all over the place, and I've waited for them to spawn for 3-4 hours with no luck.  Also note that killing them all does not make more spawn, nor does killing other things.  I'd recommend popping in here, killing all the Ghasts you find, then leaving and coming back a few hours later.  By then, if no one else is hunting them, there should be two or three up.  You'll have to kill at least ten of them to get what you need, probably more.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
