<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100299868561839></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100299868561839><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=quest.html?quest=1252&mid=100299868561839>Just finished this one.</a> <a id=fs8 href=quest.html?quest=1252&mid=100299868561839#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 13th 2:44 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This quest took me about a day and a half to complete. I went into LFay on a Friday morning, so the zone was pretty empty. I immediately picked up two rancorous ghasts on track and killed them, and got two hearts. Lucky I know! About 3 or 4 hours later, I picked up another pair of ghasts on track, killed them both and got one more heart. I stayed in LFay for about 4 more hours or so, and never saw another one spawn. Got up again early Saturday and picked up another 2 ghasts and got the fourth heart.<br><br>To pass the time in between spawns, I hunted Thistle Underbrush, he's a fairly regular spawn. He sometimes drops the Braided Ivy Cords, which are a great piece of DRU armor and can also be sold for about 200pp.<br><br>Also, I don't think that Equestrielle the Corrupted is a place holder for the ghasts. I saw one up at the same time she was.<br><br>This is an easy quest for druids, it just takes a little patience. The brownies don't aggro wolf form, so you're pretty safe in LFay as long as you can avoid Equestrielle and stay out of the Tier'Dal camps and such.<br><br>By the way, I had good luck tracking the ghasts near the GFay entrance. I just followed the path a little bit to the south and west. I picked up the ghasts every time from that same area.<br><br>Hope this helps!<br><br>Eibhleann Stormcaller<br>33 Druid, Vazaelle.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
